Write a paragraph about functions assisting top down design
Functions and proper, efficient design of them can be incredibly helpful to a programmer aiming to break their program down into smaller parts. Using functions to execute different parts of the program and then calling the functions helps to organize code into sections. 

For example, a simple calculator program could be divided into functions that will to gather input, perform the 
calculation, and give the output. it would look something like the following

[(function 1)
gather input]
[(function 2)
do calculation]
[(function 3)
output]
[call function 1]
[call function 2]
[call function 3]

The pseudocode here would outline the use of functions to break down the program, instead of all of the code being contained within main.
 Not only does this approach help with readability, but it also helps organize code in ways that are so much cleaner than a 50 line mess 
 of functionless code. It also helps for repetition, as functions can be called many times, instead of the code being rewritten in line every time.